                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-15T09:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1921—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>586. Your 398, July 13, 6 p.m. The British Government confirm with satisfaction
                    their acceptance conveyed orally on July 10th through the United States
                    Ambassador of the invitation of the <pb facs="0158" n="34" xml:id="pg_34"/>
                    United States Government to participate in a conference of the five Powers,
                    United States, Great Britain, France, Italy and Japan, to be held at mutual
                    convenience in Washington for the purpose of considering the question of
                    limitation of armaments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
